<SimplePage
  title="Privacy, KB Cafe"
  description="KB Cafe's privacy approach: the tools run entirely in your browser. Nothing you paste is uploaded, there are no accounts, no cookies, and we use only privacy-respecting aggregate analytics."
  path="/privacy"
  h1="Privacy"
>
  <p>
    Privacy isn&rsquo;t a policy bolted onto KB Cafe, it&rsquo;s how the site is built. The short version:
    <strong>your data stays on your device.</strong>
  </p>

  <h2>The tools are client-side</h2>
  <p>
    Every tool here runs entirely in your browser using JavaScript on the page. When you paste JSON, a token, a
    config, or any other input, <strong>it is never sent to a server</strong>: it&rsquo;s processed locally and
    discarded when you leave. That&rsquo;s also why the tools keep working offline once the page has loaded.
  </p>

  <h2>No accounts, no personal tracking</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>There are <strong>no sign-ups or accounts</strong> to use any tool or reference.</li>
    <li><strong>No ads, no cookies</strong>, and we never sell data.</li>
    <li>We use <strong>privacy-respecting, aggregate analytics</strong> (Plausible, cookieless) to see which pages
      and tools are useful, counts and trends only, never a profile of you. The content you put into tools is
      never part of it.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we don&rsquo;t do</h2>
  <p>
    We don&rsquo;t upload the content you put into the tools, build a profile of you, or require you to identify
    yourself. If a future feature ever needs a server (for example, an AI tool that calls a model), it will be
    clearly separated and opt-in, and this page will say so.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">Questions? Reach out via <a href="https://github.com/damnepic/kbcafe">GitHub</a>. This page describes our intent and current practice; it isn&rsquo;t legal advice.</p>
</SimplePage>
